                <head>309. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On June 15 representatives of the United States and the Dominican Republic signed
                    in Washington an “Agreement for Cooperation Between the Government of the United
                    States of America and the Government of the Dominican Republic Concerning the
                    Civil Uses of Atomic Energy.” The agreement was signed by <persName
                        corresp="#p_HHF1">Holland</persName>; <persName>Lewis L. Strauss</persName>,
                    Chairman of the United States Atomic Energy Commission; and <persName>Joaquin E.
                        Salazar</persName>, the Dominican Ambassador in the United States. For text
                    of the agreement, see 7 UST (pt. 3) 3397.</p>
            </div>
